annotationA: UMP-CMP kinase; Catalyzes the phosphorylation of pyrimidine nucleoside monophosphates at the expense of ATP. Plays an important role in de novo pyrimidine nucleotide biosynthesis. Has preference for UMP and CMP as phosphate acceptors
annotationB: CG5757, isoform A; ATP binding; thymidylate kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: dTDP biosynthetic process
